# LAMMPS Input File
# Licensed under CC BY 4.0
# A Set of Materials-Science Tutorials for the LAMMPS Simulation Package
# Appendix: structure-analysis toolkit
#
# Compare common neighbor analysis (CNA) and polyhedral template matching
# (PTM) on a thermally vibrating -- but perfectly crystalline -- aluminum
# solid at 800 K.  CNA's fixed-cutoff classification degrades with thermal
# displacement, while PTM's template fit stays robust.  Prints the fraction
# of atoms classified as fcc by each method and renders one image per
# method (blue = fcc, red = unclassified).

variable a0 equal 4.04526
variable T  equal 800.0

units metal
atom_style atomic
boundary p p p

lattice fcc ${a0}
lattice fcc 4.04526
Lattice spacing in x,y,z = 4.04526 4.04526 4.04526
region box block 0 8 0 8 0 8
create_box 1 box
Created orthogonal box = (0 0 0) to (32.36208 32.36208 32.36208)
  1 by 1 by 1 MPI processor grid
create_atoms 1 box
Created 2048 atoms
  using lattice units in orthogonal box = (0 0 0) to (32.36208 32.36208 32.36208)
  create_atoms CPU = 0.000 seconds
mass 1 26.9815
pair_style eam/fs
pair_coeff * * Al_mm.eam.fs Al
Reading eam/fs potential file Al_mm.eam.fs with DATE: 2007-06-11

velocity all create ${T} 2917 mom yes rot yes dist gaussian
velocity all create 800 2917 mom yes rot yes dist gaussian
fix md all npt temp ${T} ${T} 0.2 iso 0.0 0.0 1.0
fix md all npt temp 800 ${T} 0.2 iso 0.0 0.0 1.0
fix md all npt temp 800 800 0.2 iso 0.0 0.0 1.0
thermo 500
thermo_style custom step temp pe press lx
run 10000
Neighbor list info ...
  update: every = 1 steps, delay = 0 steps, check = yes
  max neighbors/atom: 2000, page size: 100000
  master list distance cutoff = 8.5
  ghost atom cutoff = 8.5
  binsize = 4.25, bins = 8 8 8
  1 neighbor lists, perpetual/occasional/extra = 1 0 0
  (1) pair eam/fs, perpetual
      attributes: half, newton on
      pair build: half/bin/atomonly/newton
      stencil: half/bin/3d
      bin: standard
